# Identity Mappings (Personal)

> Personal identity mappings — describe your multiple git identities and
> when each should be active. This file is .gitignored; never committed.
> Read by `~/.claude/hooks/git-identity-check.sh` at session start.

## Identities

### Identity 1: [e.g., Work — Acme Corp]

- Git name: `Your Name`
- Git email: `you@acme.com`
- Path patterns (case-insensitive substring match in cwd):
  - `acme-corp/`
  - `Cowork/acme-`

### Identity 2: [e.g., Personal Brand]

- Git name: `Your Name`
- Git email: `you@personal.dev`
- Path patterns:
  - `personal-brand/`
  - `Developer-Brand/`

## Notes

- If cwd matches no pattern → hook does nothing (ambiguous context, you verify manually)
- If cwd matches a pattern AND git config matches → hook does nothing (correct identity)
- If cwd matches a pattern AND git config mismatches → hook warns at SessionStart
